BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spinoff! The One Man Show(girl)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1655@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Cabaret
DESCRIPTION:One man sings Broadway's leading ladies — a 30-seat lounge c
 abaret\, one drink ticket included\, 21 and up.\n\nClaudio Pestana\, a reg
 ular on Atlanta's musical-theatre stages\, works through the numbers Broad
 way's most celebrated divas made famous\, from classic songbook to modern 
 showstoppers. His local credits include Jersey Boys with City Springs Thea
 tre Company and Assassins at the Jennie T. Anderson Theatre. Presented by 
 The Strand Theatre in a 30-seat lounge setting\, with one drink ticket per
  ticket and the bar open after the show\; guests must be 21 or older.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 07EtgXMAS
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:It Had to Be You
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1699@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Screwball comedy: a fading actress takes a TV commercial direc
 tor hostage on a snowbound Christmas Eve.\n\nIn Renée Taylor and Joseph B
 ologna's screwball comedy\, a fading actress snowed in on Christmas Eve ta
 kes a TV commercial director hostage\, angling to turn the standoff into b
 oth a romance and her big break. Taylor and Bologna\, the real-life marrie
 d team behind Lovers and Other Strangers\, originally wrote and starred in
  it themselves. Scott Ross directs for Merely Players. Runs through July 2
 6.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/preview-industry-n
 ight-it-had-to-be-you
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Baby Bipolar
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260709T210000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1247@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Stand-up Comedy
DESCRIPTION:Atlanta comedian Maria Mainelli's solo hour about getting a bi
 polar 1 diagnosis and deciding it doesn't run the story.\n\nMaria Mainelli
  has feelings about MyChart and at least one bad therapist review in her d
 rafts. Her solo show follows one woman from a bipolar 1 diagnosis to a lif
 e where that diagnosis doesn't have to be the bad part. Mainelli\, an Atla
 nta-based writer and comedian who has performed across the US and UK\, arr
 ives fresh off touring her debut hour\, Fly Trap\, and is a vocal mental-h
 ealth advocate. Presented by 7 Stages. Advisory: strong language and theme
 s some may find triggering.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/baby-bipolar-tickets-1989350129790
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Atlanta Experimental Fest
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260710T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260711T010000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1706@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:A festival showcase of experimental film: abstract animation\,
  personal documentaries\, surreal narratives\, and handmade cinema.\n\nA f
 estival screening devoted to independent filmmakers working outside conven
 tional storytelling. The lineup ranges across abstract animation\, persona
 l documentaries\, surreal narratives\, handmade cinema\, and work that res
 ists genre labels altogether. Presented by 7 Stages\, the Little Five Poin
 ts company with a long history of experimental programming.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://atlantafilmseries.tix.page/e/atlanta-experimental-fest
END:VEVENT
