UID:occ-117@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere musical from Gloria and Emily Estefan: Paraguay
 an kids build an orchestra out of landfill scrap.\n\nA world-premiere musi
 cal drawn from the real Recycled Orchestra of Paraguay\, in which a music 
 teacher starts an ensemble for students who have no instruments\, so they 
 make their own — paint cans and a fork become a violin\, an oil drum a c
 ello. Gloria Estefan and her daughter Emily Estefan wrote the songs\; the 
 book is by Karen Zacarías\, with Michael Greif (Rent\, Dear Evan Hansen) 
 directing and Alex Lacamoire (Hamilton) handling orchestrations. Based on 
 the documentary Landfill Harmonic. Runs through July 12.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
