 \, and fairies with a misapplied love potion.\n\nShakespeare's comedy of o
 ne moonlit night in the woods outside Athens. Four runaway lovers\, a band
  of amateur actors\, and a feuding fairy king and queen cross paths\, and 
 a mischievous sprite's love potion lands on the wrong eyelids. Before morn
 ing\, affections have swapped and the weaver Bottom is wearing a donkey's 
 head. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, performed with food and drink
  served at the table in its Elizabethan-style playhouse.
