BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Choir Boy
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-54@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tarell Alvin McCraney's coming-of-age play about a gifted quee
 r student leading his prep school's gospel choir.\n\nTarell Alvin McCraney
 's coming-of-age drama\, threaded throughout with gospel spirituals. Pharu
 s\, the most gifted singer at an elite prep school devoted to raising youn
 g Black men into leaders\, wins the coveted post of choir lead\, and finds
  that being both talented and unmistakably himself puts him at odds with c
 lassmates and tradition alike. McCraney wrote the Oscar-winning film Moonl
 ight\, and this play reached Broadway in 2019 with a Tony nomination for B
 est Play. Presented by Actor's Express.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32601
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Comedy of Errors
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260806T212000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-794@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shortest\, most slapstick comedy: two sets of tw
 ins\, one city\, and mistaken identity run gloriously amok.\n\nShakespeare
 's shortest and most farcical play: two sets of identical twins\, separate
 d at birth as infants\, end up in the same city without knowing it\, and t
 he mistaken identities pile up into wrongful beatings\, an arrest\, and ac
 cusations of madness and demonic possession. Adam King directs for the Atl
 anta Shakespeare Company\, performed with the playhouse's table seating an
 d food and drink service. Part of a three-comedy repertory alongside The T
 aming of the Shrew and Twelfth Night\; performances run through September 
 5.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
