BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Taming of the Shrew
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260807T215500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-801@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's battle-of-the-sexes comedy with an all-female+ c
 ast\, one of three comedies in an August repertory.\n\nHeadstrong Katherin
 e cannot marry off fast enough to suit her father\, and her younger sister
  cannot marry until she does. Enter Petruchio\, a bachelor as loud as Kath
 erine is sharp\, and the sparring begins. Whether the play's "taming" is c
 omedy or cruelty has been argued for centuries\; here an all-female+ cast\
 , directed by Rachel Frawley\, takes it on for the Atlanta Shakespeare Com
 pany. Part of an August repertory alternating three Shakespeare comedies\;
  this production runs through September 3.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
