CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Coltrane's A Love Supreme\, unpacked by jazz guitarist and KSU
  professor Trey Wright\; 30 seats\, 21+\, drink included.\n\nAn interactiv
 e talk on John Coltrane and A Love Supreme\, his 1965 landmark\, led by Tr
 ey Wright\, who teaches jazz guitar and jazz history at Kennesaw State. Wr
 ight is a working guitarist himself: he has played the Montreux Jazz Festi
 val\, and his trio's album Thinking Out Loud reached the first round of Gr
 ammy consideration in the jazz instrumental category. Part of the Jazz At 
 The Strand series. Admission includes one drink ticket\; seating is capped
  at 30\, and guests must be 21 or older.
