SUMMARY:All Shook Up
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260813T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260813T223000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-635@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The Elvis jukebox musical: a leather-clad roustabout shakes up
  a buttoned-down 1955 town\, Twelfth Night style.\n\nA jukebox musical bui
 lt on the Elvis Presley songbook\, with a book by Joe DiPietro (Memphis) t
 hat borrows its plot from Twelfth Night. In the summer of 1955\, a guitar-
 playing roustabout roars into a town so square its mayor enforces a Decenc
 y Act against loud music\, public necking\, and tight pants. A lovestruck 
 young mechanic named Natalie glues on a beard to get closer to him\, and t
 he romantic entanglements multiply from there\, set to "Jailhouse Rock\," 
 "Hound Dog\," and "Can't Help Falling in Love." From Marietta Theatre Comp
 any\; the show premiered on Broadway in 2005.
GEO:33.9521247;-84.5505287
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Marietta's Theatre on the Square\, 11 Whitlock Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/mariettatheatre/5266/event/1444885
END:VEVENT
