SUMMARY:Silent Film at The Strand: Sunrise (1927)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260816T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260816T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1240@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:F.W. Murnau's 1927 silent masterpiece\, scored live on the Mig
 hty Allen Theatre Organ by house organist Ron Carter.\n\nF.W. Murnau's sil
 ent classic follows a farmer torn between a seductive woman from the city 
 and the wife he has left waiting at home. It won at the very first Academy
  Awards and is still counted among the most visually inventive films ever 
 made. House organist Ron Carter accompanies live on the Strand Theatre's M
 ighty Allen\, a four-manual digital replica of a 1920s Wurlitzer complete 
 with a toy counter of train whistles\, car horns\, and gunshots. An organ 
 pops concert begins thirty minutes before showtime\; the film runs 97 minu
 tes.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
