DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-65@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tarell Alvin McCraney's coming-of-age play about a gifted quee
 r student leading his prep school's gospel choir.\n\nTarell Alvin McCraney
 's coming-of-age drama\, threaded throughout with gospel spirituals. Pharu
 s\, the most gifted singer at an elite prep school devoted to raising youn
 g Black men into leaders\, wins the coveted post of choir lead\, and finds
  that being both talented and unmistakably himself puts him at odds with c
 lassmates and tradition alike. McCraney wrote the Oscar-winning film Moonl
 ight\, and this play reached Broadway in 2019 with a Tony nomination for B
 est Play. Presented by Actor's Express.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32601
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Comedy of Errors
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T212000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-797@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shortest\, most slapstick comedy: two sets of tw
 ins\, one city\, and mistaken identity run gloriously amok.\n\nShakespeare
 's shortest and most farcical play: two sets of identical twins\, separate
 d at birth as infants\, end up in the same city without knowing it\, and t
 he mistaken identities pile up into wrongful beatings\, an arrest\, and ac
 cusations of madness and demonic possession. Adam King directs for the Atl
 anta Shakespeare Company\, performed with the playhouse's table seating an
 d food and drink service. Part of a three-comedy repertory alongside The T
 aming of the Shrew and Twelfth Night\; performances run through September 
 5.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Arsenic and Old Lace
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1372@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Kesselring's black comedy: two sweet aunts\, a body in the win
 dow seat\, and elderberry wine best declined.\n\nJoseph Kesselring's 1941 
 farce\, later the Frank Capra film with Cary Grant. Drama critic Mortimer 
 Brewster is about to announce his engagement when he finds a corpse in his
  elderly aunts' window seat\, and the ladies are entirely unbothered by it
 . Their elderberry wine\, it turns out\, carries more than a hint of arsen
 ic. Also in the house: a brother convinced he is Teddy Roosevelt and a fug
 itive sibling with a face rebuilt by a shady plastic surgeon. From the Hen
 ry Players\, a volunteer community theatre company.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/arsenic-and-old-lace-tickets-271699
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Holy Chicken Sandwich
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-535@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A new Atlanta comedy: 100 fast-food faithful camp overnight fo
 r free combos\, and something goes wrong.\n\nA new comedy from Atlanta pla
 ywright Kira Rockwell (Oh\, To Be Pure Again): on the eve of a beloved fas
 t-food chain's grand opening\, a hundred devotees camp overnight in the pa
 rking lot to win a year of free large combos. Someone among them is stirri
 ng up trouble\, and Jade\, the brand-new store manager\, has to root out t
 he saboteur before her flock descends into chaos. Lisa Adler directs for H
 orizon Theatre. Runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144303/145518
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:All Shook Up
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260821T223000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-641@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The Elvis jukebox musical: a leather-clad roustabout shakes up
  a buttoned-down 1955 town\, Twelfth Night style.\n\nA jukebox musical bui
 lt on the Elvis Presley songbook\, with a book by Joe DiPietro (Memphis) t
 hat borrows its plot from Twelfth Night. In the summer of 1955\, a guitar-
 playing roustabout roars into a town so square its mayor enforces a Decenc
 y Act against loud music\, public necking\, and tight pants. A lovestruck 
 young mechanic named Natalie glues on a beard to get closer to him\, and t
 he romantic entanglements multiply from there\, set to "Jailhouse Rock\," 
 "Hound Dog\," and "Can't Help Falling in Love." From Marietta Theatre Comp
 any\; the show premiered on Broadway in 2005.
GEO:33.9521247;-84.5505287
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Marietta's Theatre on the Square\, 11 Whitlock Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/mariettatheatre/5266/event/1444890
END:VEVENT
