SUMMARY:Annie
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260822T223000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1672@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Strouse and Charnin's 1977 Tony-winning orphan-meets-billionai
 re musical\, opening Aurora Theatre's 31st season.\n\nThe 1977 Tony winner
  for Best Musical\, drawn from Harold Gray's comic strip. In Depression-er
 a New York\, eleven-year-old Annie escapes Miss Hannigan's orphanage\, tak
 es up with a stray dog she names Sandy\, and lands a Christmas invitation 
 to billionaire Oliver Warbucks's mansion\, all while holding out hope that
  her parents will come back for her. Charles Strouse and Martin Charnin's 
 songs include "Tomorrow" and "It's the Hard Knock Life." Bethany Irby Okie
  directs for Aurora Theatre\, with company co-founder Ann-Carol Pence lead
 ing the music. Runs through September 13.
GEO:33.9568797;-83.9880958
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Lawrenceville Arts Center\, 125 N Clayton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.lvilleartscenter.com/146033/146038
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Choir Boy
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260823T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260823T161500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-67@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tarell Alvin McCraney's coming-of-age play about a gifted quee
 r student leading his prep school's gospel choir.\n\nTarell Alvin McCraney
 's coming-of-age drama\, threaded throughout with gospel spirituals. Pharu
 s\, the most gifted singer at an elite prep school devoted to raising youn
 g Black men into leaders\, wins the coveted post of choir lead\, and finds
  that being both talented and unmistakably himself puts him at odds with c
 lassmates and tradition alike. McCraney wrote the Oscar-winning film Moonl
 ight\, and this play reached Broadway in 2019 with a Tony nomination for B
 est Play. Presented by Actor's Express.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32601
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Twelfth Night
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260823T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260823T170500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-810@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shipwreck comedy of twins\, disguise\, and yello
 w stockings\, in the Atlanta Shakespeare Company's three-comedy August rep
 ertory.\n\nShipwrecked on the coast of Illyria and believing her twin brot
 her drowned\, Viola disguises herself as a young man and enters Duke Orsin
 o's service\, promptly tangling herself into a love triangle. Meanwhile\, 
 a forged letter convinces the pompous steward Malvolio that yellow stockin
 gs are the way to his lady's heart. Mary Ruth Ralston directs for the Atla
 nta Shakespeare Company\, with dinner-table seating and drink service duri
 ng the show. Part of the August Threepeat\, a repertory rotating three Sha
 kespeare comedies nightly\; this one plays through September 4.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Arsenic and Old Lace
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260823T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260823T163000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1374@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Kesselring's black comedy: two sweet aunts\, a body in the win
 dow seat\, and elderberry wine best declined.\n\nJoseph Kesselring's 1941 
 farce\, later the Frank Capra film with Cary Grant. Drama critic Mortimer 
 Brewster is about to announce his engagement when he finds a corpse in his
  elderly aunts' window seat\, and the ladies are entirely unbothered by it
 . Their elderberry wine\, it turns out\, carries more than a hint of arsen
 ic. Also in the house: a brother convinced he is Teddy Roosevelt and a fug
 itive sibling with a face rebuilt by a shady plastic surgeon. From the Hen
 ry Players\, a volunteer community theatre company.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/arsenic-and-old-lace-tickets-271699
END:VEVENT
