BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Purpose
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260828T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260828T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-118@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Branden Jacobs-Jenkins' Tony- and Pulitzer-winning drama of a 
 Black political dynasty's reunion coming undone.\n\nThe Jaspers are a Chic
 ago dynasty of ministers\, activists\, and changemakers\, gathering for a 
 long-overdue family reunion. When a young outsider arrives with questions 
 nobody wants asked\, the family's carefully guarded secrets start to surfa
 ce over one evening. Branden Jacobs-Jenkins (Appropriate\, An Octoroon) wo
 n both the 2025 Tony Award for Best Play and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama 
 for this one\; the New York Post called it "unstoppably fierce\, funny\, a
 nd ruthless." Keith Arthur Bolden directs for the Alliance Theatre\, in a 
 co-production with McCarter Theatre Center\; runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164228/164267
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Taming of the Shrew
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260828T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260828T215500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-805@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's battle-of-the-sexes comedy with an all-female+ c
 ast\, one of three comedies in an August repertory.\n\nHeadstrong Katherin
 e cannot marry off fast enough to suit her father\, and her younger sister
  cannot marry until she does. Enter Petruchio\, a bachelor as loud as Kath
 erine is sharp\, and the sparring begins. Whether the play's "taming" is c
 omedy or cruelty has been argued for centuries\; here an all-female+ cast\
 , directed by Rachel Frawley\, takes it on for the Atlanta Shakespeare Com
 pany. Part of an August repertory alternating three Shakespeare comedies\;
  this production runs through September 3.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
