 judge\, and Mrs. Lovett's suspiciously well-stocked pie shop.\n\nStephen S
 ondheim and Hugh Wheeler's 1979 musical thriller\, based on Christopher Bo
 nd's play. Benjamin Barker returns from wrongful exile as Sweeney Todd\, r
 eopens his barbershop above Mrs. Lovett's failing pie shop\, and sharpens 
 his razors for the judge who destroyed his family. His customers\, meanwhi
 le\, start finding their way into the pies. Charlie Miller directs for Ons
 tage Atlanta\; runs through August 30.
