SUMMARY:Arsenic and Old Lace
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260829T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260829T163000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1376@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Kesselring's black comedy: two sweet aunts\, a body in the win
 dow seat\, and elderberry wine best declined.\n\nJoseph Kesselring's 1941 
 farce\, later the Frank Capra film with Cary Grant. Drama critic Mortimer 
 Brewster is about to announce his engagement when he finds a corpse in his
  elderly aunts' window seat\, and the ladies are entirely unbothered by it
 . Their elderberry wine\, it turns out\, carries more than a hint of arsen
 ic. Also in the house: a brother convinced he is Teddy Roosevelt and a fug
 itive sibling with a face rebuilt by a shady plastic surgeon. From the Hen
 ry Players\, a volunteer community theatre company.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
