BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Purpose
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260829T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260829T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-119@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Branden Jacobs-Jenkins' Tony- and Pulitzer-winning drama of a 
 Black political dynasty's reunion coming undone.\n\nThe Jaspers are a Chic
 ago dynasty of ministers\, activists\, and changemakers\, gathering for a 
 long-overdue family reunion. When a young outsider arrives with questions 
 nobody wants asked\, the family's carefully guarded secrets start to surfa
 ce over one evening. Branden Jacobs-Jenkins (Appropriate\, An Octoroon) wo
 n both the 2025 Tony Award for Best Play and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama 
 for this one\; the New York Post called it "unstoppably fierce\, funny\, a
 nd ruthless." Keith Arthur Bolden directs for the Alliance Theatre\, in a 
 co-production with McCarter Theatre Center\; runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164228/164269
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Twelfth Night
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260829T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260829T220500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-811@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shipwreck comedy of twins\, disguise\, and yello
 w stockings\, in the Atlanta Shakespeare Company's three-comedy August rep
 ertory.\n\nShipwrecked on the coast of Illyria and believing her twin brot
 her drowned\, Viola disguises herself as a young man and enters Duke Orsin
 o's service\, promptly tangling herself into a love triangle. Meanwhile\, 
 a forged letter convinces the pompous steward Malvolio that yellow stockin
 gs are the way to his lady's heart. Mary Ruth Ralston directs for the Atla
 nta Shakespeare Company\, with dinner-table seating and drink service duri
 ng the show. Part of the August Threepeat\, a repertory rotating three Sha
 kespeare comedies nightly\; this one plays through September 4.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
