DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1679@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Strouse and Charnin's 1977 Tony-winning orphan-meets-billionai
 re musical\, opening Aurora Theatre's 31st season.\n\nThe 1977 Tony winner
  for Best Musical\, drawn from Harold Gray's comic strip. In Depression-er
 a New York\, eleven-year-old Annie escapes Miss Hannigan's orphanage\, tak
 es up with a stray dog she names Sandy\, and lands a Christmas invitation 
 to billionaire Oliver Warbucks's mansion\, all while holding out hope that
  her parents will come back for her. Charles Strouse and Martin Charnin's 
 songs include "Tomorrow" and "It's the Hard Knock Life." Bethany Irby Okie
  directs for Aurora Theatre\, with company co-founder Ann-Carol Pence lead
 ing the music. Runs through September 13.
GEO:33.9568797;-83.9880958
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Lawrenceville Arts Center\, 125 N Clayton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.lvilleartscenter.com/146033/146052
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street (2026)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T173000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-692@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Sondheim's 1979 revenge musical: a wronged barber\, a corrupt 
 judge\, and Mrs. Lovett's suspiciously well-stocked pie shop.\n\nStephen S
 ondheim and Hugh Wheeler's 1979 musical thriller\, based on Christopher Bo
 nd's play. Benjamin Barker returns from wrongful exile as Sweeney Todd\, r
 eopens his barbershop above Mrs. Lovett's failing pie shop\, and sharpens 
 his razors for the judge who destroyed his family. His customers\, meanwhi
 le\, start finding their way into the pies. Charlie Miller directs for Ons
 tage Atlanta\; runs through August 30.
GEO:33.7932167;-84.2681503
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:OnStage Atlanta\, 3041 N Decatur Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/onstageatlanta/612/event/1436133
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:On Golden Pond
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T173000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-707@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Ernest Thompson's comedy-drama of a long marriage\, a prickly 
 father-daughter reunion\, and one Maine summer.\n\nErnest Thompson's play 
 about Ethel and Norman Thayer\, spending their 48th summer at their lake h
 ouse in the Maine woods as Norman turns 80 and his memory starts slipping 
 into cantankerously morbid jokes. The birthday brings their daughter Chels
 ea\, her boyfriend\, and his teenage son\, stirring up old grievances betw
 een father and daughter while Norman finds an unexpected fishing partner i
 n the boy. Best known from the 1981 film with Henry Fonda and Katharine He
 pburn. From Players Guild at Sugar Hill.
GEO:34.1070667;-84.0353528
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Eagle Theater\, 5029 W Broad St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36627/performance/11797885/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Twelfth Night
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260830T171500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1196@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shipwreck comedy: twins separated at sea\, a wom
 an in disguise\, and a love triangle nobody can untangle.\n\nShakespeare's
  comedy of mistaken identity. Shipwrecked and separated from her twin brot
 her\, Viola disguises herself as a young man and enters Duke Orsino's serv
 ice\, only to fall for him while carrying his love letters to a countess w
 ho promptly falls for her. Meanwhile a forged letter and a pair of yellow 
 stockings send the pompous steward Malvolio into humiliating raptures. Fro
 m Pumphouse Players\, one of Georgia's oldest continuously operating commu
 nity theatre companies.
GEO:34.1644344;-84.7971239
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Pumphouse Players\, 114 W Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/twelfth-night-tickets-1989767660636
END:VEVENT
