DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1682@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Strouse and Charnin's 1977 Tony-winning orphan-meets-billionai
 re musical\, opening Aurora Theatre's 31st season.\n\nThe 1977 Tony winner
  for Best Musical\, drawn from Harold Gray's comic strip. In Depression-er
 a New York\, eleven-year-old Annie escapes Miss Hannigan's orphanage\, tak
 es up with a stray dog she names Sandy\, and lands a Christmas invitation 
 to billionaire Oliver Warbucks's mansion\, all while holding out hope that
  her parents will come back for her. Charles Strouse and Martin Charnin's 
 songs include "Tomorrow" and "It's the Hard Knock Life." Bethany Irby Okie
  directs for Aurora Theatre\, with company co-founder Ann-Carol Pence lead
 ing the music. Runs through September 13.
GEO:33.9568797;-83.9880958
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Lawrenceville Arts Center\, 125 N Clayton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.lvilleartscenter.com/146033/146055
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:On Golden Pond
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T173000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-709@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Ernest Thompson's comedy-drama of a long marriage\, a prickly 
 father-daughter reunion\, and one Maine summer.\n\nErnest Thompson's play 
 about Ethel and Norman Thayer\, spending their 48th summer at their lake h
 ouse in the Maine woods as Norman turns 80 and his memory starts slipping 
 into cantankerously morbid jokes. The birthday brings their daughter Chels
 ea\, her boyfriend\, and his teenage son\, stirring up old grievances betw
 een father and daughter while Norman finds an unexpected fishing partner i
 n the boy. Best known from the 1981 film with Henry Fonda and Katharine He
 pburn. From Players Guild at Sugar Hill.
GEO:34.1070667;-84.0353528
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Eagle Theater\, 5029 W Broad St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36627/performance/11801767/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Parade
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T173000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-929@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Uhry and Brown's Tony-winning musical of the 1913 Leo Frank ca
 se\, a history that ended in Marietta itself.\n\nAlfred Uhry and Jason Rob
 ert Brown's musical dramatization of the Leo Frank case: a Jewish factory 
 manager from Brooklyn\, convicted in 1913 of murdering thirteen-year-old w
 orker Mary Phagan while an ambitious prosecutor and a sensation-hungry pre
 ss fanned the flames. At the show's center is Frank's marriage\, as his wi
 fe Lucille grows from distant spouse into his fiercest advocate. The origi
 nal won Tony Awards for Uhry's book and Brown's score\, and the 2023 Broad
 way revival won Best Revival of a Musical. The history it dramatizes ended
  with Frank's 1915 lynching in Marietta\, the very town where this perform
 ance is staged.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06VOU1MAO
END:VEVENT
