BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Comedy of Errors
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260905T212000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-800@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's shortest\, most slapstick comedy: two sets of tw
 ins\, one city\, and mistaken identity run gloriously amok.\n\nShakespeare
 's shortest and most farcical play: two sets of identical twins\, separate
 d at birth as infants\, end up in the same city without knowing it\, and t
 he mistaken identities pile up into wrongful beatings\, an arrest\, and ac
 cusations of madness and demonic possession. Adam King directs for the Atl
 anta Shakespeare Company\, performed with the playhouse's table seating an
 d food and drink service. Part of a three-comedy repertory alongside The T
 aming of the Shrew and Twelfth Night\; performances run through September 
 5.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/august-threepeat-sh
 rew-comedy-of-errors-and-twelfth-night-in-repertory
END:VEVENT
