UID:occ-1688@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Strouse and Charnin's 1977 Tony-winning orphan-meets-billionai
 re musical\, opening Aurora Theatre's 31st season.\n\nThe 1977 Tony winner
  for Best Musical\, drawn from Harold Gray's comic strip. In Depression-er
 a New York\, eleven-year-old Annie escapes Miss Hannigan's orphanage\, tak
 es up with a stray dog she names Sandy\, and lands a Christmas invitation 
 to billionaire Oliver Warbucks's mansion\, all while holding out hope that
  her parents will come back for her. Charles Strouse and Martin Charnin's 
 songs include "Tomorrow" and "It's the Hard Knock Life." Bethany Irby Okie
  directs for Aurora Theatre\, with company co-founder Ann-Carol Pence lead
 ing the music. Runs through September 13.
