SUMMARY:Parade
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260919T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260919T173000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-939@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Uhry and Brown's Tony-winning musical of the 1913 Leo Frank ca
 se\, a history that ended in Marietta itself.\n\nAlfred Uhry and Jason Rob
 ert Brown's musical dramatization of the Leo Frank case: a Jewish factory 
 manager from Brooklyn\, convicted in 1913 of murdering thirteen-year-old w
 orker Mary Phagan while an ambitious prosecutor and a sensation-hungry pre
 ss fanned the flames. At the show's center is Frank's marriage\, as his wi
 fe Lucille grows from distant spouse into his fiercest advocate. The origi
 nal won Tony Awards for Uhry's book and Brown's score\, and the 2023 Broad
 way revival won Best Revival of a Musical. The history it dramatizes ended
  with Frank's 1915 lynching in Marietta\, the very town where this perform
 ance is staged.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06Ves9MAC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Purpose
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260919T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260919T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-139@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Branden Jacobs-Jenkins' Tony- and Pulitzer-winning drama of a 
 Black political dynasty's reunion coming undone.\n\nThe Jaspers are a Chic
 ago dynasty of ministers\, activists\, and changemakers\, gathering for a 
 long-overdue family reunion. When a young outsider arrives with questions 
 nobody wants asked\, the family's carefully guarded secrets start to surfa
 ce over one evening. Branden Jacobs-Jenkins (Appropriate\, An Octoroon) wo
 n both the 2025 Tony Award for Best Play and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama 
 for this one\; the New York Post called it "unstoppably fierce\, funny\, a
 nd ruthless." Keith Arthur Bolden directs for the Alliance Theatre\, in a 
 co-production with McCarter Theatre Center\; runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164228/164284
END:VEVENT
