SUMMARY:Purpose
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260920T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260920T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-141@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Branden Jacobs-Jenkins' Tony- and Pulitzer-winning drama of a 
 Black political dynasty's reunion coming undone.\n\nThe Jaspers are a Chic
 ago dynasty of ministers\, activists\, and changemakers\, gathering for a 
 long-overdue family reunion. When a young outsider arrives with questions 
 nobody wants asked\, the family's carefully guarded secrets start to surfa
 ce over one evening. Branden Jacobs-Jenkins (Appropriate\, An Octoroon) wo
 n both the 2025 Tony Award for Best Play and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama 
 for this one\; the New York Post called it "unstoppably fierce\, funny\, a
 nd ruthless." Keith Arthur Bolden directs for the Alliance Theatre\, in a 
 co-production with McCarter Theatre Center\; runs through September 20.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164228/164285
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Shrek (2001)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1661@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:DreamWorks' 2001 fairy-tale spoof on the big screen — Mike M
 yers' ogre\, Eddie Murphy's Donkey\, 89 minutes\, PG.\n\nThe 2001 DreamWor
 ks comedy that won the first-ever Oscar for Best Animated Feature\, back o
 n a big screen. An ogre who just wants his swamp to himself strikes a deal
  with the fussy Lord Farquaad: rescue Princess Fiona\, get the fairy-tale 
 squatters off his land. Mike Myers voices Shrek in the Scottish accent he 
 insisted on re-recording every line to get\, with Eddie Murphy\, Cameron D
 iaz\, and John Lithgow rounding out the cast\, plus a Smash Mouth-heavy so
 undtrack that dates it precisely and fondly. Loosely based on William Stei
 g's picture book. 89 minutes\, rated PG.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 075VwnMAE
END:VEVENT
