BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fences
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260923T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-993@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:August Wilson's Pulitzer winner: a former Negro League star in
  1950s Pittsburgh\, at war with his son's dreams.\n\nAugust Wilson's 1985 
 drama\, sixth in his ten-play Pittsburgh Cycle and winner of the Pulitzer 
 Prize and the Tony for Best Play. Troy Maxson was a Negro League baseball 
 star before the color barrier broke\; now he hauls trash\, builds a fence 
 in his yard\, and refuses to let his son chase a college football scholars
 hip\, convinced the game will break the boy the way it broke him. Theatric
 al Outfit produces in partnership with Dominion Entertainment Group and th
 e Alabama Shakespeare Festival\, a two-state revival of the play.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
