BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Measure for Measure
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260924T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260924T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1458@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's problem play: a disguised duke\, a puritan deput
 y\, and a novice nun bargaining for her brother's life.\n\nThe Duke of Vie
 nna orders his city's dormant morality laws enforced\, hands power to his 
 strict deputy Angelo\, and pretends to leave town. In truth he stays\, dis
 guised as a friar\, to watch what his deputy does with the job. What Angel
 o does is sentence young Claudio to death for fornication\, and when Claud
 io's sister Isabella\, a novice nun\, comes to plead for mercy\, he names 
 a price she cannot pay with a clear conscience. The First Folio filed it w
 ith the comedies\, but its executions and moral bargaining have long earne
 d it the label of problem play. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, per
 formed with tavern table seating and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/measure-for-measure
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Philadelphia Story
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260925T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260925T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-599@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Philip Barry's 1939 high-society comedy: a socialite's second 
 wedding\, crashed by her ex-husband and two tabloid journalists.\n\nPhilip
  Barry's 1939 comedy of the privileged class. Tracy Lord\, headstrong daug
 hter of the Philadelphia Lords\, is set to marry a successful young snob w
 hen her ex-husband and a pair of tabloid journalists descend on the family
  estate for the wedding weekend. Barry wrote the role for Katharine Hepbur
 n\, who backed the play with her own money and carried it into the 1940 fi
 lm with Cary Grant and James Stewart. Darci Rose Wells directs for Lionhea
 rt Theatre\, where every ticket includes dessert at intermission\; runs th
 rough September 27.
GEO:33.9421741;-84.2112431
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Lionheart Theatre\, 10 College St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/35819/production/1276719/performance/1181318
 5
END:VEVENT
