DESCRIPTION:Frederick Knott's 1966 thriller: a blind woman\, three con men
 \, and a doll worth killing for.\n\nFrederick Knott's 1966 suspense thrill
 er\, the same one Audrey Hepburn filmed a year later. Susy Hendrix is blin
 d\, alone in her apartment\, and the target of con artists who believe a m
 issing doll is hidden there. As their schemes tighten around her\, she has
  only her wits and her ears to work with. A revival from Cherokee Theatre\
 , brought back by patron request\; recommended for ages 12 and up.
GEO:34.2365417;-84.4902423
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Canton Theatre\, 171 E Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/cherokeetheatre/1960/event/1465840
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fences
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-997@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:August Wilson's Pulitzer winner: a former Negro League star in
  1950s Pittsburgh\, at war with his son's dreams.\n\nAugust Wilson's 1985 
 drama\, sixth in his ten-play Pittsburgh Cycle and winner of the Pulitzer 
 Prize and the Tony for Best Play. Troy Maxson was a Negro League baseball 
 star before the color barrier broke\; now he hauls trash\, builds a fence 
 in his yard\, and refuses to let his son chase a college football scholars
 hip\, convinced the game will break the boy the way it broke him. Theatric
 al Outfit produces in partnership with Dominion Entertainment Group and th
 e Alabama Shakespeare Festival\, a two-state revival of the play.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Measure for Measure
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T164500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1461@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's problem play: a disguised duke\, a puritan deput
 y\, and a novice nun bargaining for her brother's life.\n\nThe Duke of Vie
 nna orders his city's dormant morality laws enforced\, hands power to his 
 strict deputy Angelo\, and pretends to leave town. In truth he stays\, dis
 guised as a friar\, to watch what his deputy does with the job. What Angel
 o does is sentence young Claudio to death for fornication\, and when Claud
 io's sister Isabella\, a novice nun\, comes to plead for mercy\, he names 
 a price she cannot pay with a clear conscience. The First Folio filed it w
 ith the comedies\, but its executions and moral bargaining have long earne
 d it the label of problem play. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, per
 formed with tavern table seating and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/measure-for-measure
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sparrows (1926)
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260927T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-942@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Film Screening
DESCRIPTION:Mary Pickford's 1926 silent melodrama\, screened with live acc
 ompaniment on the Mighty Allen Theatre Organ.\n\nMary Pickford plays Molly
 \, the oldest of a band of orphans held captive on a baby farm deep in an 
 alligator-infested swamp\, who plots their escape when the children's crue
 l keeper decides to be rid of one of them. Part of the Strand Theatre's Si
 lent Film Series\, with house organist Ron Carter providing a live score o
 n the Mighty Allen Theatre Organ\, whose digital toy counter supplies whis
 tles\, thunder\, and gunshots on cue. An organ pops concert begins thirty 
 minutes before the film. Runs 1 hour 49 minutes\; not rated.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06X9ttMAC
END:VEVENT
