BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mexodus
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261003T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261003T163000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-142@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Two-performer hip-hop musical on the Underground Railroad's so
 uthern route into Mexico\, with every song looped live onstage.\n\nThe Und
 erground Railroad also ran south: thousands of enslaved people crossed the
  Rio Grande to Mexico\, where slavery had already been abolished. Creators
  Brian Quijada and Nygel D. Robinson play every role and build each song's
  arrangement live on a looping station\, following Henry\, a man fleeing b
 ondage in Texas\, and Carlos\, the Mexican stranger who becomes his ally. 
 The New York Times called the Off-Broadway run "a dazzling showcase" for t
 he sheer joy of music-making. David Mendizábal directs this Atlanta debut
  from the Alliance Theatre\; runs through October 16.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164197/164250
END:VEVENT
