BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Like Father
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-158@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:New folk-pop musical: after her father's arrest\, a teenager's
  family becomes true-crime podcast fodder.\n\nA world-premiere coming-of-a
 ge musical written by Jacob Ryan Smith and Caroline Pernick\, from Allianc
 e Theatre. Seventeen-year-old Chris\, reeling from her father's arrest\, l
 ands with the estranged mother and stepfather she barely knows\, until a h
 it true-crime podcast drags the family's buried past into public view. The
  folk-pop score draws on the stories of relatives left behind by infamous 
 killers\, and on an industry that has grown to 250 million listeners. Tina
 she Kajese-Bolden directs\; the show won the first Open Jar Broadway Shark
  Tank and runs through November 15.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164244/164488
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jazz Talks with Trey Wright
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T203000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1237@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Coltrane's A Love Supreme\, unpacked by jazz guitarist and KSU
  professor Trey Wright\; 30 seats\, 21+\, drink included.\n\nAn interactiv
 e talk on John Coltrane and A Love Supreme\, his 1965 landmark\, led by Tr
 ey Wright\, who teaches jazz guitar and jazz history at Kennesaw State. Wr
 ight is a working guitarist himself: he has played the Montreux Jazz Festi
 val\, and his trio's album Thinking Out Loud reached the first round of Gr
 ammy consideration in the jazz instrumental category. Part of the Jazz At 
 The Strand series. Admission includes one drink ticket\; seating is capped
  at 30\, and guests must be 21 or older.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06zRKnMAM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Macbeth
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1464@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's Scottish tragedy of witches\, prophecy\, and a c
 ouple who won't wait for fate\, from the Atlanta Shakespeare Company.\n\nT
 hree witches hail a victorious Scottish general as a future king\, and he 
 and his wife decide not to leave the crown to chance. Shakespeare's shorte
 st tragedy traces their climb from prophecy to murder to guilt that will n
 ot wash off. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, performed with food an
 d drink served at your table. A 2025 Suzi Bass Awards Recommended Show.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/macbeth
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ripcord
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1602@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:David Lindsay-Abaire's comedy of two mismatched retirement-hom
 e roommates and the prank war that spirals between them.\n\nDavid Lindsay-
 Abaire's comedy set in a shared room at the Bristol Place Senior Living Fa
 cility\, where the cantankerous Abby wants her sunny upper-floor quarters 
 to herself and the relentlessly cheerful new arrival Marilyn refuses to bu
 dge. What starts as a bet between the two women spirals into increasingly 
 outrageous pranks\, and each round unearths secrets both would prefer stay
 ed buried. From Stage Door Theatre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11823392/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Paths To God
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261008T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-563@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145610
END:VEVENT
