BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ripcord
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261010T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261010T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1605@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:David Lindsay-Abaire's comedy of two mismatched retirement-hom
 e roommates and the prank war that spirals between them.\n\nDavid Lindsay-
 Abaire's comedy set in a shared room at the Bristol Place Senior Living Fa
 cility\, where the cantankerous Abby wants her sunny upper-floor quarters 
 to herself and the relentlessly cheerful new arrival Marilyn refuses to bu
 dge. What starts as a bet between the two women spirals into increasingly 
 outrageous pranks\, and each round unearths secrets both would prefer stay
 ed buried. From Stage Door Theatre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11823390/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:i never asked for a gofundme
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261010T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261010T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-42@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere play: top surgery mistaken for breast cancer\
 , and a small-town GoFundMe nobody asked for.\n\nMillie and her partner Av
 ery are riding out Avery's recovery from gender-affirming top surgery in M
 illie's hometown of Mobile\, Alabama. Then a nosy evangelical family frien
 d misreads the surgery as a breast-cancer fight and launches a GoFundMe on
  the couple's behalf\, making them the talk of the town and the recipients
  of donations they never wanted. Whether to keep the money\, and what keep
 ing it would cost them\, is the question. A world premiere from Actor's Ex
 press.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32801
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Paths To God
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261010T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261010T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-566@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145611
END:VEVENT
