CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:New folk-pop musical: after her father's arrest\, a teenager's
  family becomes true-crime podcast fodder.\n\nA world-premiere coming-of-a
 ge musical written by Jacob Ryan Smith and Caroline Pernick\, from Allianc
 e Theatre. Seventeen-year-old Chris\, reeling from her father's arrest\, l
 ands with the estranged mother and stepfather she barely knows\, until a h
 it true-crime podcast drags the family's buried past into public view. The
  folk-pop score draws on the stories of relatives left behind by infamous 
 killers\, and on an industry that has grown to 250 million listeners. Tina
 she Kajese-Bolden directs\; the show won the first Open Jar Broadway Shark
  Tank and runs through November 15.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164244/169466
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Paths To God
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261015T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261015T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-569@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145613
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:i never asked for a gofundme
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261016T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261016T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-46@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere play: top surgery mistaken for breast cancer\
 , and a small-town GoFundMe nobody asked for.\n\nMillie and her partner Av
 ery are riding out Avery's recovery from gender-affirming top surgery in M
 illie's hometown of Mobile\, Alabama. Then a nosy evangelical family frien
 d misreads the surgery as a breast-cancer fight and launches a GoFundMe on
  the couple's behalf\, making them the talk of the town and the recipients
  of donations they never wanted. Whether to keep the money\, and what keep
 ing it would cost them\, is the question. A world premiere from Actor's Ex
 press.
GEO:33.7817253;-84.4160629
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:King Plow Arts Center\, 887 W Marietta St NW\, Suite J-107
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://purchase.actors-express.com/EventAvailability?EventId=32801
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mexodus
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261016T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261016T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-157@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Two-performer hip-hop musical on the Underground Railroad's so
 uthern route into Mexico\, with every song looped live onstage.\n\nThe Und
 erground Railroad also ran south: thousands of enslaved people crossed the
  Rio Grande to Mexico\, where slavery had already been abolished. Creators
  Brian Quijada and Nygel D. Robinson play every role and build each song's
  arrangement live on a looping station\, following Henry\, a man fleeing b
 ondage in Texas\, and Carlos\, the Mexican stranger who becomes his ally. 
 The New York Times called the Off-Broadway run "a dazzling showcase" for t
 he sheer joy of music-making. David Mendizábal directs this Atlanta debut
  from the Alliance Theatre\; runs through October 16.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164197/164264
END:VEVENT
