DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261016T210000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1345@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Dance Performance
DESCRIPTION:A narrated\, kid-friendly Cinderella ballet from Atlanta Balle
 t 2 — 75 minutes with intermission\, ages 4 and up.\n\nThe glass-slipper
  fairy tale as one of Atlanta Ballet's Family Ballets: a short\, narrated 
 production from Atlanta Ballet 2\, the company's second troupe\, built so 
 kids as young as four can follow the story. Bruce Wells choreographs\, and
  a narrator walks young audiences through the plot as the dancers tell it.
  Runs an hour and fifteen minutes\, including a 20-minute intermission.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
