CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Christopher Durang's Chekhov-riffing comedy: a movie-star sist
 er\, her young boyfriend\, and a family farmhouse up for sale.\n\nChristop
 her Durang's comedy borrows its names and its moods from Chekhov\, then le
 ts them loose in present-day Pennsylvania. Siblings Vanya and Sonia have s
 pent their quiet lives in the family farmhouse\; their movie-star sister M
 asha blows in for the weekend with her much younger boyfriend Spike and an
 nounces she's selling the place. Rivalry\, regret\, and a costume party fo
 llow. The play won the 2013 Tony Award for Best Play\; this production com
 es from Arcadia Theater.
