BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Superior Donuts
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261023T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261023T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1312@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tracy Letts's comedy-drama of a burned-out donut shop owner an
 d the young writer who shakes him awake.\n\nTracy Letts\, the Pulitzer win
 ner behind August: Osage County\, in a gentler mode: a former '60s radical
  presides over his fading donut shop in Chicago's Uptown until Franco\, a 
 bright young Black writer\, turns up looking for work and full of plans to
  fix the place. Reviewing the 2008 Steppenwolf premiere\, the New York Tim
 es's Charles Isherwood called it "insubstantial and sweet" yet "hard to di
 slike." Robby Myles directs for Authenticity Theater. Runs through October
  31.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://authenticitytheater.ludus.com/index.php?sections=events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Like Father
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261024T163000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-171@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:New folk-pop musical: after her father's arrest\, a teenager's
  family becomes true-crime podcast fodder.\n\nA world-premiere coming-of-a
 ge musical written by Jacob Ryan Smith and Caroline Pernick\, from Allianc
 e Theatre. Seventeen-year-old Chris\, reeling from her father's arrest\, l
 ands with the estranged mother and stepfather she barely knows\, until a h
 it true-crime podcast drags the family's buried past into public view. The
  folk-pop score draws on the stories of relatives left behind by infamous 
 killers\, and on an industry that has grown to 250 million listeners. Tina
 she Kajese-Bolden directs\; the show won the first Open Jar Broadway Shark
  Tank and runs through November 15.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164244/164517
END:VEVENT
