DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T191500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-579@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Five ICU nurses\, $3 million missing\, one scandal: a world-pr
 emiere comedy from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith.\n\nA world premiere 
 from Atlanta playwright Kelundra Smith\, writer of The Wash. When $3 milli
 on goes missing at Morey Medical Center and fingers point at the ICU's fiv
 e nurses\, everybody's worst behavior comes out. Smith drew on interviews 
 with real Atlanta nurses to write about what it means to give your life to
  a job that doesn't love you back. Commissioned through Horizon Theatre's 
 Black Women Speak program\; runs through November 8.
GEO:33.7620155;-84.3525137
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Horizon Theatre\, 1083 Austin Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.horizontheatre.com/144305/145633
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Like Father
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261025T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-174@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:New folk-pop musical: after her father's arrest\, a teenager's
  family becomes true-crime podcast fodder.\n\nA world-premiere coming-of-a
 ge musical written by Jacob Ryan Smith and Caroline Pernick\, from Allianc
 e Theatre. Seventeen-year-old Chris\, reeling from her father's arrest\, l
 ands with the estranged mother and stepfather she barely knows\, until a h
 it true-crime podcast drags the family's buried past into public view. The
  folk-pop score draws on the stories of relatives left behind by infamous 
 killers\, and on an industry that has grown to 250 million listeners. Tina
 she Kajese-Bolden directs\; the show won the first Open Jar Broadway Shark
  Tank and runs through November 15.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164244/164501
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Buena Vista Social Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261027T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261027T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1348@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:National touring production of the Broadway musical behind Cub
 a's landmark 1997 album\, sung entirely in Spanish.\n\nThe Broadway musica
 l built from the songs of the 1997 Buena Vista Social Club album: singer O
 mara Portuondo\, once celebrated across Cuba as the "Queen of Feeling\," h
 as long vanished from the spotlight when a young record producer arrives w
 ith one more chance at the studio. The story moves between 1990s Havana an
 d the musicians' younger selves in the 1950s\, and the score — son\, dan
 zón\, bolero — is performed entirely in Spanish. Book by Marco Ramirez\
 , with choreography by Justin Peck and Patricia Delgado\; the show won a S
 pecial Tony Award for its live onstage musicians and a Grammy for its cast
  album. A national touring production.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=BVS&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
