BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Superior Donuts
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261028T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261028T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1315@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tracy Letts's comedy-drama of a burned-out donut shop owner an
 d the young writer who shakes him awake.\n\nTracy Letts\, the Pulitzer win
 ner behind August: Osage County\, in a gentler mode: a former '60s radical
  presides over his fading donut shop in Chicago's Uptown until Franco\, a 
 bright young Black writer\, turns up looking for work and full of plans to
  fix the place. Reviewing the 2008 Steppenwolf premiere\, the New York Tim
 es's Charles Isherwood called it "insubstantial and sweet" yet "hard to di
 slike." Robby Myles directs for Authenticity Theater. Runs through October
  31.
GEO:33.7639125;-84.3509364
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:7 Stages Theatre\, 1105 Euclid Ave NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://authenticitytheater.ludus.com/index.php?sections=events
END:VEVENT
