BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Silent Night
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261115T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261115T173100
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-373@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Opera
DESCRIPTION:Kevin Puts's Pulitzer-winning opera about the 1914 Christmas t
 ruce\, sung in five languages.\n\nKevin Puts's first opera\, with a libret
 to by Mark Campbell adapted from the film Joyeux Noël\, dramatizes the re
 al Christmas truce of 1914\, when German\, French\, and Scottish soldiers 
 put down their weapons and met in no-man's-land. A German tenor's carol\, 
 answered by a Scottish bagpipe\, sparks the cease-fire\; the generals back
  at headquarters are considerably less moved. The score earned Puts a Puli
 tzer in 2012. Sung in English\, French\, German\, Italian\, and Latin. Fro
 m The Atlanta Opera\; runs through November 15.
GEO:33.88471;-84.4585962
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Cobb Energy Performing Arts Centre\, 2800 Cobb Galleria Pkwy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.atlantaopera.org/145901/145905
END:VEVENT
