BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Othello
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261119T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261119T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1486@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's tragedy of jealousy — Iago whispers\, and a gr
 eat general's faith in his wife unravels.\n\nShakespeare's tragedy of a Ve
 netian general undone not by war but by his own ensign: Iago\, passed over
  for promotion\, sets out to convince Othello that his new wife Desdemona 
 has been unfaithful\, using little more than insinuation and a misplaced h
 andkerchief. Iago is one of the longest roles in the canon\, and watching 
 him work the room is half the horror. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company
 \, performed Elizabethan-style with food and drink served at your table.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/othello
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Last Gift
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T203000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1690@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere Christmas play about a crotchety nursing-home r
 esident and the young child who wins him over.\n\nA new play set in a nurs
 ing home around the Christmas holidays\, where a young child works on the 
 defenses of a crotchety old man. Atlanta playwright Earnest Lewis\, also a
  children's book author\, wrote it\, weaving in elder care\, adoption\, lo
 neliness\, and family. Dave Di Pietro directs this world premiere for the 
 Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts. Runs through November 22.
GEO:33.6671075;-84.0180229
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts\, 910 Center St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://conyersarts.org/calender-of-events/the-last-gift/
END:VEVENT
