BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:It's a Wonderful Life: A Live Radio Play
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-952@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Capra's 1946 Christmas classic restaged as a live 1940s radio 
 broadcast\, with onstage foley effects and actors doubling dozens of roles
 .\n\nThe story of George Bailey\, the Bedford Falls building-and-loan man 
 who hits bottom one snowy Christmas Eve and gets shown what his town would
  look like if he'd never been born. This adaptation of Frank Capra's 1946 
 film plays out as a period radio broadcast: a small ensemble at vintage mi
 crophones voicing dozens of characters\, with every footstep\, door slam\,
  and ringing bell made live by a foley artist in full view. Presented by T
 he Strand Theatre.
GEO:33.9536122;-84.5492054
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Strand Theatre\, 117 N Park Square
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://thestrand.my.salesforce-sites.com/ticket/#/instances/a0FPs0000
 06WSlhMAG
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Other Desert Cities
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1152@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Jon Robin Baitz's Pulitzer-finalist family drama: a daughter's
  tell-all memoir detonates a Palm Springs Christmas.\n\nJon Robin Baitz's 
 drama\, a finalist for the 2012 Pulitzer Prize\, unfolds over Christmas Ev
 e 2004 in Palm Springs. Brooke Wyeth comes home after six years away with 
 a finished memoir that digs into the death of her brother\, a chapter her 
 staunchly Republican parents have spent decades keeping closed. Her aunt S
 ilda\, fresh from rehab and firmly on the other side of the political fenc
 e\, is also in the house. The festive reunion turns into a fight over memo
 ry\, loyalty\, and who gets to tell the family's story. Presented by Merel
 y Players.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/other-desert-citie
 s-2026-11-20-19-30
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Death Becomes Her
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261120T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1359@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The Broadway musical of the 1992 camp classic: two frenemies\,
  one youth potion\, and a grudge built to outlast death.\n\nThe musical ad
 apted from the 1992 Robert Zemeckis film: fading actress Madeline Ashton a
 nd long-suffering writer Helen Sharp have spent decades as frenemies\, and
  the feud turns supernatural when a mysterious potion restores their youth
  and makes the grudge eternal. Book by Marco Pennette\, with songs by Juli
 a Mattison and Noel Carey. Tony winner Christopher Gattelli directs and ch
 oreographs. Variety called it "a laugh-filled\, tuneful musical to die for
 ."
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=DBH&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
