BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Christmas Story: The Musical
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261220T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261220T160000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1277@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Ralphie's quest for a Red Ryder BB gun\, sung: the Pasek and P
 aul musical of the 1983 holiday film.\n\nThe 1983 movie that runs on a loo
 p every December\, turned Broadway musical with songs by Benj Pasek and Ju
 stin Paul (later of Dear Evan Hansen) and a book by Joseph Robinette. Nine
 -year-old Ralphie Parker schemes toward the one gift every adult swears wi
 ll shoot his eye out: an Official Red Ryder carbine-action BB gun. The leg
  lamp\, the tongue on the flagpole\, and the pink bunny suit all make it o
 nstage\, in a score The New York Times called "likable" and "perky." From 
 Arcadia Theater.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/christmas-story-the-musical-tickets-279858
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:All is Calm: The Christmas Truce of 1914
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261220T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261220T160000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-388@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Peter Rothstein's a cappella retelling of the WWI Christmas tr
 uce\, built from soldiers' letters and period songs.\n\nOn Christmas Eve 1
 914\, soldiers along the Western Front laid down their rifles\, crossed no
 -man's land\, and sang together. Peter Rothstein's documentary-style music
 al tells that true story through trench songs\, patriotic tunes\, and caro
 ls\, sung a cappella and woven with the soldiers' own words from letters a
 nd journals. Music by Erick Lichte and Timothy C. Takach. Presented by The
  Atlanta Opera as part of its Discoveries series.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.theatricaloutfit.org/whats-on/all-is-calm-the-christmas-tr
 uce-of-1914/book/64403
END:VEVENT
