BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Christmas Carol
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261226T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261226T161500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-232@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Dickens's Scrooge-and-three-ghosts classic in David H. Bell's 
 adaptation with live music\, from the Alliance Theatre.\n\nCharles Dickens
 's 1843 tale of Ebenezer Scrooge\, the miser visited by the ghosts of Chri
 stmas Past\, Present\, and Yet to Come on a single night of reckoning. The
  Alliance Theatre's annual production uses David H. Bell's adaptation\, st
 aged with live music and a large company of characters. Amanda Watkins dir
 ects\, building on Leora Morris's original staging. Runs through December 
 27.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164230/164956
END:VEVENT
