DESCRIPTION:Bizet's tragedy of obsession: a soldier\, a bullfighter\, and 
 the woman who refuses to be owned.\n\nGeorges Bizet's 1875 opera\, set in 
 Seville: Carmen\, a factory worker who answers to no one\, throws a flower
  at the one soldier ignoring her. Don José picks it up and unravels — d
 eserting the army\, abandoning his sweetheart\, and following Carmen into 
 the mountains\, only to lose her to the bullfighter Escamillo. The score h
 olds some of opera's most familiar melodies\, the Habanera and the Toreado
 r Song among them\, though its first Paris audiences were scandalized by s
 o much lawlessness on the Opéra-Comique stage. From The Atlanta Opera.
GEO:33.88471;-84.4585962
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Cobb Energy Performing Arts Centre\, 2800 Cobb Galleria Pkwy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.atlantaopera.org/145907/145975
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Water For Elephants
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270202T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270202T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1728@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Sara Gruen's Depression-era circus novel as a musical\, on nat
 ional tour after premiering in Atlanta before Broadway.\n\nDuring the Depr
 ession\, a young man who has just lost everything hops a moving train and 
 lands among the Benzini Brothers circus\, where his veterinary training\, 
 an untrainable elephant named Rosie\, and the ringmaster's wife reshape hi
 s life\, all remembered through the eyes of his older self. Rick Elice ada
 pted the book from Sara Gruen's 2006 novel\, with a score by PigPen Theatr
 e Co. and Rosie brought to life through puppetry. The show premiered in At
 lanta at the Alliance Theatre in 2023 before a Broadway run that earned se
 ven Tony nominations\, including Best Musical. This is the national tourin
 g production.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=WAT&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
