DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1521@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:This performance is Romeo and Juliet\, half of a repertory pai
 ring Shakespeare's tragedy with Much Ado About Nothing.\n\nTwo Shakespeare
  plays about love\, running in repertory from the Atlanta Shakespeare Comp
 any. This performance is Romeo and Juliet: two teenagers fall for each oth
 er across a family feud\, with one well-intentioned Friar trying to hold i
 t all together. Kelly Criss directs the company's 23rd anniversary product
 ion of the tragedy. On alternate dates\, Alejandra Ruiz directs Much Ado A
 bout Nothing\, the Beatrice-and-Benedick comedy of two confirmed singles t
 oo witty for their own good. Table seating with food and drink service dur
 ing the show\; the repertory runs through February 28.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
