 ry-romeo-and-juliet-and-much-ado-about-nothing
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alice in Neverland
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-264@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere musical: twenty years on\, a disenchanted gro
 wn Alice tries to find Wonderland again — and lands in Neverland instead
 .\n\nA new Alliance musical from Phil Kenny and Reston Williams. Two decad
 es after the rabbit hole\, Alice's life has come apart\; chasing the happi
 ness she remembers\, she sets out for Wonderland and crash-lands somewhere
  far more dangerous. A story about reclaiming childhood and what it costs 
 to never grow up.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164232/164299
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What the Constitution Means to Me
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1085@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Heidi Schreck's Tony-nominated play revisiting her teenage Con
 stitution-debate speeches\, in its Atlanta premiere.\n\nHeidi Schreck put 
 herself through college giving prize-winning speeches about the Constituti
 on at American Legion halls\; her 2019 Broadway play returns to those cont
 ests\, toggling between her fifteen-year-old self and the woman she became
 . What starts as a debate exercise opens into the stories of the women in 
 her family and how the document actually treated them — funny\, personal
 \, and pointed by turns. A Tony nominee for Best Play and a Pulitzer final
 ist\, it gets its Atlanta premiere from Theatrical Outfit.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Women of Willow Creek
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1165@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Six women\, 28 days\, one rehabilitation facility: a drama of 
 recovery from Merely Players.\n\nA drama that follows Harper and five othe
 r women through a 28-day stay in a rehabilitation facility\, their recover
 ies tangled together as the days count down. The subject matter is heavy a
 nd unflinching — suicide\, eating disorders\, self-harm\, substance use\
 , and PTSD all figure in — but the play finds real humor in the darkest 
 corners of the ward. From Merely Players\, a small non-equity company that
  stages work reflecting its community's diversity.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/the-women-of-willo
 w-creek-2027-02-27-19-30
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stage Kiss
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270227T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1291@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Sarah Ruhl's comedy: two exes cast as lovers in a creaky 1930s
  melodrama\, and the kissing gets complicated.\n\nSarah Ruhl's backstage c
 omedy about two actors with a shared romantic past who land opposite each 
 other as the leads in a forgotten 1930s melodrama. The script requires the
 m to kiss\, repeatedly\, and the line between playing lovers and being the
 m starts to dissolve. A community production from Arcadia Theater.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/stage-kiss-tickets-279866
END:VEVENT
