BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Black Comedy
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270305T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270305T221500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-450@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Peter Shaffer's 1965 farce with the lighting reversed: when th
 e power fails\, the stage lights up.\n\nPeter Shaffer's one-act farce runs
  on a single inspired gimmick: light and dark are swapped\, so when the po
 wer blows\, the stage blazes and the audience watches everyone grope blind
 ly through the chaos. A young sculptor has borrowed his absent neighbor's 
 antiques to impress a millionaire art collector\, and the blackout brings 
 the neighbor home early\, along with an ex-mistress and a string of unexpe
 cted guests. One Guardian critic called the original 'an uproarious piece 
 of slapstick vaudeville.' A Cherokee Theatre production\, recommended for 
 ages 12 and up.
GEO:34.2365417;-84.4902423
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Canton Theatre\, 171 E Main St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/cherokeetheatre/1960/event/1465857
END:VEVENT
