BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What the Constitution Means to Me
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270307T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270307T163000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1091@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Heidi Schreck's Tony-nominated play revisiting her teenage Con
 stitution-debate speeches\, in its Atlanta premiere.\n\nHeidi Schreck put 
 herself through college giving prize-winning speeches about the Constituti
 on at American Legion halls\; her 2019 Broadway play returns to those cont
 ests\, toggling between her fifteen-year-old self and the woman she became
 . What starts as a debate exercise opens into the stories of the women in 
 her family and how the document actually treated them — funny\, personal
 \, and pointed by turns. A Tony nominee for Best Play and a Pulitzer final
 ist\, it gets its Atlanta premiere from Theatrical Outfit.
GEO:33.757035;-84.389486
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Theatrical Outfit\, 84 Luckie St NW
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Julius Caesar
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270307T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270307T164500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1530@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Shakespeare's tragedy of conspiracy and assassination in Rome\
 , from the Atlanta Shakespeare Company.\n\nShakespeare's 1599 tragedy of t
 he plot against Julius Caesar: senators convinced they are saving the repu
 blic\, a murder on the Senate floor\, and Marc Antony's funeral oration th
 at turns the city against them. The play's real center is Brutus\, torn be
 tween loyalty to his friend and fear of what Caesar might become. From the
  Atlanta Shakespeare Company\, with artistic director Jeff Watkins playing
  Caesar and Kenneth Wigley as Antony\, performed in the company's Elizabet
 han-style playhouse with table seating and food and drink service during t
 he show.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/julius-caesar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alice in Neverland
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270309T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270309T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-272@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere musical: twenty years on\, a disenchanted gro
 wn Alice tries to find Wonderland again — and lands in Neverland instead
 .\n\nA new Alliance musical from Phil Kenny and Reston Williams. Two decad
 es after the rabbit hole\, Alice's life has come apart\; chasing the happi
 ness she remembers\, she sets out for Wonderland and crash-lands somewhere
  far more dangerous. A story about reclaiming childhood and what it costs 
 to never grow up.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164232/164305
END:VEVENT
