BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Flying Dutchman
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270313T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270313T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-397@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Opera
DESCRIPTION:Wagner's ghost-ship opera: a captain cursed to sail forever\, 
 ashore once every seven years seeking love.\n\nRichard Wagner's early oper
 a built on the old maritime legend of a phantom ship doomed never to make 
 port. Its captain is allowed ashore once every seven years to search for a
  woman whose faithful love can break the curse\, and in the sea captain's 
 daughter Senta he may have found her. Wagner's storm-tossed score made thi
 s his first enduring success. Presented by the Atlanta Opera.
GEO:33.88471;-84.4585962
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Cobb Energy Performing Arts Centre\, 2800 Cobb Galleria Pkwy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.atlantaopera.org/145974/145978
END:VEVENT
