BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Shakespeare Out of a Hat: Julius Caesar
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270315T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270315T204500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1542@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Improv Comedy
DESCRIPTION:Improv meets Shakespeare: actors draw their Julius Caesar role
 s from a hat two minutes before the show begins.\n\nThe Atlanta Shakespear
 e Company's classically trained actors know the script\; nobody knows who'
 s playing whom until roles come out of a hat moments before curtain. The p
 lay in question is Julius Caesar\, the conspiracy drama that made the Ides
  of March infamous\, so Brutus could be anyone. A one-night-only event\, p
 erformed with the company's usual table seating and food and drink service
  during the show.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/shakespeare-out-of-
 a-hat-julius-caesar-on-the-ides-of-march
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Flying Dutchman
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270316T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270316T220000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-398@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Opera
DESCRIPTION:Wagner's ghost-ship opera: a captain cursed to sail forever\, 
 ashore once every seven years seeking love.\n\nRichard Wagner's early oper
 a built on the old maritime legend of a phantom ship doomed never to make 
 port. Its captain is allowed ashore once every seven years to search for a
  woman whose faithful love can break the curse\, and in the sea captain's 
 daughter Senta he may have found her. Wagner's storm-tossed score made thi
 s his first enduring success. Presented by the Atlanta Opera.
GEO:33.88471;-84.4585962
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Cobb Energy Performing Arts Centre\, 2800 Cobb Galleria Pkwy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tickets.atlantaopera.org/145974/145979
END:VEVENT
