BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alice in Neverland
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270404T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270404T163000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-299@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:A world-premiere musical: twenty years on\, a disenchanted gro
 wn Alice tries to find Wonderland again — and lands in Neverland instead
 .\n\nA new Alliance musical from Phil Kenny and Reston Williams. Two decad
 es after the rabbit hole\, Alice's life has come apart\; chasing the happi
 ness she remembers\, she sets out for Wonderland and crash-lands somewhere
  far more dangerous. A story about reclaiming childhood and what it costs 
 to never grow up.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164232/164335
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270404T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270404T161500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-307@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere satire: a pristine Connecticut living room\, th
 ree centuries\, and the question of who gets believed.\n\nAlanna Coby's ne
 w play opens on affluent women gathered in a spotless Connecticut living r
 oom\, certain of their own virtue — until a young working-class mother w
 ith nowhere else to go walks in. From there the play cracks time open acro
 ss three centuries\, tracing how class\, gender\, and power keep reproduci
 ng themselves under the cover of charity and good manners\, and the comedy
  curdles into something darker. A finalist for the Alliance's own Kendeda 
 Graduate Playwriting Competition and the Princess Grace Awards\, it gets i
 ts world premiere from the Alliance Theatre\, directed by Tinashe Kajese-B
 olden. Runs through April 25.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164248/164575
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Streetcar Named Desire
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270404T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270404T160000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1297@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tennessee Williams' 1947 tragedy of Blanche DuBois\, her illus
 ions\, and the brother-in-law who sees through them.\n\nTennessee Williams
 ' 1947 drama\, still one of the towering American plays. After losing the 
 family home to creditors\, Blanche DuBois arrives in a cramped New Orleans
  apartment to live with her sister Stella and a brother-in-law\, Stanley K
 owalski\, who has no patience for her airs or her illusions. A flicker of 
 hope appears in Stanley's courtly friend Mitch\, but Blanche's past keeps 
 circling closer. From Arcadia Theater\, Alpharetta's community company.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/a-streetcar-named-desire-tickets-279868
END:VEVENT
