BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lauren Gunderson's The Book of Will
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270410T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270410T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1547@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Gunderson's true story of the two actors who saved half of Sha
 kespeare's plays by printing the First Folio.\n\nAfter Shakespeare's death
 \, his fellow actors Henry Condell and John Heminges set out to collect an
 d publish his plays as the First Folio\, without which roughly half of the
 m would have vanished. Lauren Gunderson\, the Atlanta-born writer who has 
 repeatedly topped American Theatre's list of the country's most-produced l
 iving playwrights\, spins the history into a story of friendship\, grief\,
  and stubborn devotion to the words. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\
 , performed with the tavern's table seating and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/lauren-gundersons-t
 he-book-of-will
END:VEVENT
