BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Clean House
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270411T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270411T191500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1167@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Sarah Ruhl's whimsical comedy about a Brazilian housekeeper wh
 o'd rather craft the perfect joke than clean.\n\nSarah Ruhl's play\, a 200
 5 Pulitzer finalist\, starts with a mess: Lane\, a doctor\, has hired Mati
 lde\, a housekeeper who dreams of being a comedian and refuses to clean. L
 ane's sister Virginia\, who finds cleaning a calling\, secretly takes over
  the housework\, and the discoveries in the laundry pull the whole househo
 ld somewhere stranger and sadder. Variety praised its "screwy poetry and p
 enetrating wisdom." Presented by Merely Players.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/the-clean-house-20
 27-04-11-17-00
END:VEVENT
