 peare by inventing the world's first musical.\n\nThe 2015 Broadway comedy 
 by Karey and Wayne Kirkpatrick with John O'Farrell\, set in 1595: brothers
  Nick and Nigel Bottom run a theatre troupe stuck in the shadow of a rock-
 star Shakespeare. Desperate for an edge\, Nick pays a soothsayer to glimps
 e the future of theatre and learns it involves people bursting into song m
 id-scene. The score is wall-to-wall musical-theatre in-jokes\; the show ea
 rned ten Tony nominations. From the Henry Players community theatre compan
 y.
