DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270416T223000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-728@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Mary Rodgers's 1959 musical spoof of The Princess and the Pea\
 , from Players Guild at Sugar Hill.\n\nThe 1959 musical comedy that gave C
 arol Burnett her Broadway debut\, with music by Mary Rodgers and lyrics by
  Marshall Barer\, retelling The Princess and the Pea the way it supposedly
  really happened. Queen Aggravain has rigged an impassable test for any pr
 incess who wants to marry her son\, and nobody else in the kingdom can wed
  until he does. Then Winnifred the Woebegone arrives\, having swum the cas
 tle moat to get there. Presented by Players Guild at Sugar Hill.
GEO:34.1070667;-84.0353528
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Eagle Theater\, 5029 W Broad St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
