BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270417T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270417T161500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-319@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere satire: a pristine Connecticut living room\, th
 ree centuries\, and the question of who gets believed.\n\nAlanna Coby's ne
 w play opens on affluent women gathered in a spotless Connecticut living r
 oom\, certain of their own virtue — until a young working-class mother w
 ith nowhere else to go walks in. From there the play cracks time open acro
 ss three centuries\, tracing how class\, gender\, and power keep reproduci
 ng themselves under the cover of charity and good manners\, and the comedy
  curdles into something darker. A finalist for the Alliance's own Kendeda 
 Graduate Playwriting Competition and the Princess Grace Awards\, it gets i
 ts world premiere from the Alliance Theatre\, directed by Tinashe Kajese-B
 olden. Runs through April 25.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164248/164578
END:VEVENT
