 peare by inventing the world's first musical.\n\nThe 2015 Broadway comedy 
 by Karey and Wayne Kirkpatrick with John O'Farrell\, set in 1595: brothers
  Nick and Nigel Bottom run a theatre troupe stuck in the shadow of a rock-
 star Shakespeare. Desperate for an edge\, Nick pays a soothsayer to glimps
 e the future of theatre and learns it involves people bursting into song m
 id-scene. The score is wall-to-wall musical-theatre in-jokes\; the show ea
 rned ten Tony nominations. From the Henry Players community theatre compan
 y.
GEO:33.4486439;-84.1418279
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:The Henry Players Theater\, 136 Hood St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.simpletix.com/e/something-rotten-tickets-269298
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lauren Gunderson's The Book of Will
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270418T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270418T164500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1552@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Gunderson's true story of the two actors who saved half of Sha
 kespeare's plays by printing the First Folio.\n\nAfter Shakespeare's death
 \, his fellow actors Henry Condell and John Heminges set out to collect an
 d publish his plays as the First Folio\, without which roughly half of the
 m would have vanished. Lauren Gunderson\, the Atlanta-born writer who has 
 repeatedly topped American Theatre's list of the country's most-produced l
 iving playwrights\, spins the history into a story of friendship\, grief\,
  and stubborn devotion to the words. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\
 , performed with the tavern's table seating and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
