 ode=NOT&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Last Five Years
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270418T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270418T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1142@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Jason Robert Brown's two-person musical: her story told backwa
 rd\, his forward\, crossing once on their wedding day.\n\nJason Robert Bro
 wn's song-cycle musical traces five years between Jamie\, a novelist whose
  career takes off fast\, and Cathy\, an actress whose career won't. The tr
 ick is the structure: Cathy tells her story in reverse\, starting at the m
 arriage's end\, while Jamie moves forward from the first date\, and the tw
 o timelines meet only once\, at the wedding. Brown wrote it after his own 
 divorce\, and the score ranges from klezmer to pop ballad. Presented by Ju
 nction Playhouse.
GEO:33.4739853;-84.5085251
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shipyard at Trilith\, 125 Shepperton Wy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/the-junction-playhouse-presents-
 the-last-five-years
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270418T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270418T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-322@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere satire: a pristine Connecticut living room\, th
 ree centuries\, and the question of who gets believed.\n\nAlanna Coby's ne
 w play opens on affluent women gathered in a spotless Connecticut living r
 oom\, certain of their own virtue — until a young working-class mother w
 ith nowhere else to go walks in. From there the play cracks time open acro
 ss three centuries\, tracing how class\, gender\, and power keep reproduci
 ng themselves under the cover of charity and good manners\, and the comedy
  curdles into something darker. A finalist for the Alliance's own Kendeda 
 Graduate Playwriting Competition and the Princess Grace Awards\, it gets i
 ts world premiere from the Alliance Theatre\, directed by Tinashe Kajese-B
 olden. Runs through April 25.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164248/164569
END:VEVENT
