BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270424T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270424T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-327@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:World-premiere satire: a pristine Connecticut living room\, th
 ree centuries\, and the question of who gets believed.\n\nAlanna Coby's ne
 w play opens on affluent women gathered in a spotless Connecticut living r
 oom\, certain of their own virtue — until a young working-class mother w
 ith nowhere else to go walks in. From there the play cracks time open acro
 ss three centuries\, tracing how class\, gender\, and power keep reproduci
 ng themselves under the cover of charity and good manners\, and the comedy
  curdles into something darker. A finalist for the Alliance's own Kendeda 
 Graduate Playwriting Competition and the Princess Grace Awards\, it gets i
 ts world premiere from the Alliance Theatre\, directed by Tinashe Kajese-B
 olden. Runs through April 25.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164248/164573
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Clean House
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270424T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270424T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1172@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Sarah Ruhl's whimsical comedy about a Brazilian housekeeper wh
 o'd rather craft the perfect joke than clean.\n\nSarah Ruhl's play\, a 200
 5 Pulitzer finalist\, starts with a mess: Lane\, a doctor\, has hired Mati
 lde\, a housekeeper who dreams of being a comedian and refuses to clean. L
 ane's sister Virginia\, who finds cleaning a calling\, secretly takes over
  the housework\, and the discoveries in the laundry pull the whole househo
 ld somewhere stranger and sadder. Variety praised its "screwy poetry and p
 enetrating wisdom." Presented by Merely Players.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/the-clean-house-20
 27-04-24-19-30
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lauren Gunderson's The Book of Will
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270424T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270424T214500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1555@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Gunderson's true story of the two actors who saved half of Sha
 kespeare's plays by printing the First Folio.\n\nAfter Shakespeare's death
 \, his fellow actors Henry Condell and John Heminges set out to collect an
 d publish his plays as the First Folio\, without which roughly half of the
 m would have vanished. Lauren Gunderson\, the Atlanta-born writer who has 
 repeatedly topped American Theatre's list of the country's most-produced l
 iving playwrights\, spins the history into a story of friendship\, grief\,
  and stubborn devotion to the words. From the Atlanta Shakespeare Company\
 , performed with the tavern's table seating and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
