BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Guess Who's Coming to Dinner
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270604T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270604T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1705@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Todd Kreidler's stage adaptation of the 1967 film: a daughter'
 s surprise fiancé tests her progressive parents' ideals.\n\nTodd Kreidler
  adapts the 1967 film that starred Sidney Poitier\, Spencer Tracy\, and Ka
 tharine Hepburn\, released the same year the Supreme Court struck down ban
 s on interracial marriage in Loving v. Virginia. A liberal couple's daught
 er comes home unannounced with a new fiancé\, and a celebratory dinner tu
 rns into a long night of the family arguing with its own principles about 
 love\, race\, and acceptance. Funnier than its subject suggests\, and poin
 ted where it counts. Presented by Merely Players.
GEO:33.9031178;-84.2776526
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Merely Players Presents\, 3785 King Ave
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.merelyplayerspresents.com/event-details/guess-whos-coming-
 to-dinner-06-04-27
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:John Proctor is the Villain
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270605T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270605T161500
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-348@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Kimberly Belflower's Tony-nominated comedy-drama: Georgia teen
 s study The Crucible and start doubting its hero.\n\nAn English class in a
  one-stoplight Georgia town takes up The Crucible\, and the students begin
  to suspect Arthur Miller's hero isn't the good guy after all. Kimberly Be
 lflower's play mixes pop music\, first crushes\, and feminist fury into wh
 at The New York Times called a "vital\, hilarious\, [and] thrilling" portr
 ait of teenage girlhood. After a 2025 Broadway run that earned seven Tony 
 nominations\, including Best Play\, it makes its Georgia debut from the Al
 liance Theatre\, directed by Autumn Angelettie. Runs through June 6.
GEO:33.7893845;-84.3846553
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Woodruff Arts Center\, 1280 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://my.alliancetheatre.org/164234/164357
END:VEVENT
