DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270801T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270801T170000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-859@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The 2002 Tony-winning musical: a big-haired Baltimore teen dan
 ces her way onto TV and into the civil rights fight.\n\nBaltimore\, 1962: 
 Tracy Turnblad\, big of hair and bigger of heart\, wins a spot on a local 
 TV dance show and starts campaigning to integrate it. Marc Shaiman and Sco
 tt Wittman's score runs on 1960s dance-party pop and rhythm and blues\, ad
 apted from John Waters's 1988 film\; the Broadway production took eight To
 ny Awards\, including Best Musical. Presented by Southside Theatre Guild\,
  an all-volunteer community theatre running since 1973.
GEO:33.5672762;-84.5821546
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Southside Theatre Guild\, 20 W Campbellton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tockify.com/stgevents/detail/1032/1816540200000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Price is Ri-FUNNY
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270807
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270808
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1599@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Improv Comedy
DESCRIPTION:Live improv comedy — scenes and characters built on the spot
  from audience suggestions.\n\nA night of improv comedy: nothing scripted\
 , everything built in the moment from whatever the audience throws out\, s
 o no two performances are the same show. Presented by Southside Theatre Gu
 ild\, an all-volunteer community theatre in operation since 1973 and home 
 to the improv troupe Southside Sidekicks.
GEO:33.5672762;-84.5821546
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Southside Theatre Guild\, 20 W Campbellton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tockify.com/stgevents/detail/1068/1817611200000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Every Brilliant Thing
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270814T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270814T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-1645@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Duncan Macmillan's one-performer play about a list of things w
 orth living for\, with the audience holding pieces of it.\n\nDuncan Macmil
 lan and Jonny Donahoe's one-performer play about a narrator who\, at age s
 even\, responds to his mother's suicide attempt by starting a list of ever
 ything worth living for. The list grows through college\, marriage\, and a
  depression of his own. The audience keeps the show running: some hold num
 bered cards and shout out entries on cue (rollercoasters\, people falling 
 over)\, and a few get drafted into roles on the spot. From Stage Door Thea
 tre.
GEO:33.9447222;-84.3319444
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Stage Door Theatre\, 5339 Chamblee Dunwoody Rd
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://ci.ovationtix.com/36385/performance/11825838/selecttickets
END:VEVENT
